{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC20","role":"sampleCode","title":"Broaden your reach with Siri Event Suggestions"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"kind":"article","sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc20\/10197","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (29 min)","isActive":true}},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10197-broaden-your-reach-with-siri-event-suggestions"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Whether you’re hosting event information in your app, on the web, or in an email, Siri Event Suggestions can help people keep track of their commitments — without compromising their privacy. We’ll show you how to set up your reservations so that they automatically show up in the Calendar app and how to work with the Siri Event Suggestions APIs for iOS and Markup for web and email.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10197-Broaden-your-reach-with-Siri-Event-Suggestions","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Siri Event Suggestions are now also on macOS Big Sur and on the simulator","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"What-is-Siri-Event-Suggestions","text":"What is Siri Event Suggestions?","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Makes it easy to get your event from your app into Calendar"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The system uses on-device intelligence to streamline everyday interactions with your events:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"on the lock screen, Siri can notify you when it’s time to leave for a restaurant reservation, based on local traffic conditions."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"on Maps, you get a Siri Suggestion, making getting directions to the airport to catch a flight is as easy as just one tap."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Siri can also proactively suggest turning on Do Not Disturb, so you can stay focused on what matters, like the movie you’re about to watch."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Siri can even provide a suggestion to check-in for your flight right on your lock screen."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"New-categories-and-platforms","text":"New categories and platforms","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Previously:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Restaurants booking"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Car rentals"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Train"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Movies","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lodging"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Ticketed Events","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Flights"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"New:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bus"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Boat"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"New-ways-to-donate-events","text":"New ways to donate events","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Beside apps you can now donate events with Mail.app and Safari.app:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"to do you need to embed the event web markup within the HTML of your website or emails."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"leverages a web standard called ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/schema.org\/docs\/documents.html","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"supports both JSON-LD and Microdata","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"JSON-LD example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"xml","code":["<script type=\"application\/ld+json\">","{","  \"@context\": \"http:\/\/schema.org\",","  \"@type\": \"FoodEstablishmentReservation\",","  \"reservationStatus\": \"http:\/\/schema.org\/ReservationConfirmed\",","  \"reservationId\": \"IWDSCA\",","  \"partySize\": \"2\",","  \"reservationFor\": {","    \"@type\": \"FoodEstablishment\",","    \"name\": \"EPIC Steak\",","    \"startDate\": \"2020-06-26T19:30:00-07:00\",","    \"telephone\": \"(415)369-9955\"","    \"address\": {","      \"@type\": \"http:\/\/schema.org\/PostalAddress\",","      \"streetAddress\": \"369 The Embarcadero\",","      \"addressLocality\": \"San Francisco\"","      \"addressRegion\": \"CA\",","      \"postalCode\": \"95105\",","      \"addressCountry\": \"USA\"","    }","  }","}","<\/script>"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Microdata example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"xml","code":["<div itemscope itemtype=\"FoodEstablishmentReservation\"> ","  <link itemprop=\"reservationStatus\" href=\"http:\/\/schema.org\/ReservationConfirmed\"\/>","  <meta itemprop=\"reservationId\" content=\"IWDSCA\"\/>","  <meta itemprop=\"partySize\" content=\"2\"\/>","  <div itemprop=\"reservationFor\" itemscope itemtype=\"FoodEstablishment\">","    <meta itemprop=\"name\" content=\"EPIC Steak\"\/>","    <meta itemprop=\"startDate\" content=\"2020-06-26T19:30:00-07:00\"\/>","    <meta itemprop=\"telephone\" content=\"(415)369-9955\"\/>","    <div itemprop=\"address\" itemscope itemtype=\"PostalAddress\">","      <meta itemprop=\"streetAddress\" content=\"369 The Embarcadero\"\/>","      <meta itemprop=\"addressLocality\" content=\"San Francisco\"\/>","      <meta itemprop=\"addressRegion\" content=\"CA\"\/>","      <meta itemprop=\"postalCode\" content=\"95105\"\/>","      <meta itemprop=\"addressCountry\" content=\"USA\"\/>","    <\/div>","  <\/div>","<\/div>"],"type":"codeListing"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As long as the reservation identifier stays the same, we can use the same markup format to update the event as well.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the event gets canceled, update the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reservationStatus"},{"type":"text","text":" to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"http:\/\/schema.org\/ReservationCancelled"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Requirements","text":"Requirements","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"you must register your domain at "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/contact\/request\/siri-events\/"},{"type":"text","text":" where you can submit your domain and samples of your markup."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"your website must use HTTPS, and that your emails have a valid DKIM signature.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Testing","text":"Testing","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To enable your domain for testing, either:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"open the Developer Settings and enable ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Allow Any Domain on iOS"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"use the command below on the Mac:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":null,"code":["defaults write com.apple.suggestions SuggestionsAllowAnyDomainForMarkup -bool true"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To enable local testing, either:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"open the Developer Settings and enable ","type":"text"},{"code":"Allow Unverified Sources","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"use the command below on the Mac:","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":null,"code":["defaults write com.apple.suggestions SuggestionsAllowUnverifiedSourceForMarkup -bool true"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Guidelines","text":"Guidelines","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use appropriate "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reservationStatus"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ISO8601"},{"type":"text","text":" format for dates and time"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reservationId"},{"text":" consistent for updates and canceled reservations","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Donations-overview","text":"Donations overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC20-10197-overview","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To donate to Siri, the app first maps its reservation details into "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/sirikit\/inreservation","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" objects."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"INReservation","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" contains the details about the reservation shown in the app.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"INReservation"},{"type":"text","text":" objects are added to an intent response that, together with the intent, forms the interaction, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/sirikit\/ininteraction","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", that the app donates to Siri."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Once donated, Siri may create one or more Calendar events and notify the user that the reservations were added to their Siri Event Suggestions Calendar.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To get more details, or to manage the reservation, we want people to easily get back into your app, so we put a “Show in App” button right in Calendar to make this easy."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the “Show in App” button is pressed, the system will construct an "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/sirikit\/ingetreservationdetailsintent","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" containing information about the reservation the user wants to view."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This "},{"code":"INGetReservationDetailsIntent","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" uses the container and item reference from the donation that was used to create the event."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A reservation may consist of one or more parts. For example, in a flight reservation with multiple legs, each leg is one part of the reservation and must be represented as an individual ","type":"text"},{"code":"INReservation","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" object with a unique ","type":"text"},{"code":"item reference","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"WWDC20-10197-itemReference","type":"image"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can choose any identifier you’d like, as long as it’s unique and it enables you to find a specific part of the reservation to show when being launched","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"if the booking consists of one part only, like a dinner, you can use the reservation number as item reference","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"if the booking consists of multiple parts, like a round-trip flight, each flight\/leg needs to have its own unique item reference (for example the ticket number)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"if the app is not installed on a device, instead of the “Show in App” button there will be a “Show in Safari” button: pressing this will open the URL you set in Safari, so the user can view their reservation details on your website."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Make sure you adopt this new URL property, since calendar events will be synced to all the users’ devices, some of which may not have your app installed."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Debugging-Donations","text":"Debugging Donations","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When your app\/website\/email donates reservation details, they may be processed asynchronously by different parts of the system: it’s not always possible to let your app know if something went wrong."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To help you debug issues during development, you can view donation logs in the Console.app (needs Big Sur):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"select the device you’re debuggin"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"filter by ","type":"text"},{"code":"siri-event-suggestions","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" category","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"donate again"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Written-By","text":"Written By","type":"heading"},{"numberOfColumns":5,"columns":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"zntfdr","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":1},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Federico Zanetello","anchor":"Federico-Zanetello"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributed Notes","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/zntfdr.dev"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"size":4}],"type":"row"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Missing anything? Corrections? "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Related-Sessions","text":"Related Sessions","type":"heading"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC23-10052-Discover-Calendar-and-EventKit","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10068-Whats-new-in-SiriKit-and-Shortcuts","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10086-Design-for-intelligence-Apps-evolved","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10087-Design-for-intelligence-Make-friends-with-The-System","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10088-Design-for-intelligence-Discover-new-opportunities","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10200-Design-for-intelligence-Meet-people-where-they-are","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-243-Integrating-with-Siri-Event-Suggestions"],"style":"list","type":"links"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Legal Notice","type":"text"}]}],"type":"small"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All content copyright © 2012 – 2024 Apple Inc. All rights reserved."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Swift, the Swift logo, Swift Playgrounds, Xcode, Instruments, Cocoa Touch, Touch ID, FaceID, iPhone, iPad, Safari, Apple Vision, Apple Watch, App Store, iPadOS, watchOS, visionOS, tvOS, Mac, and macOS are trademarks of Apple Inc., registered in the U.S. and other countries."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This website is not made by, affiliated with, nor endorsed by Apple."}],"type":"small"}]}],"references":{"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/sirikit/inreservation":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/sirikit\/inreservation","title":"INReservation","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"INReservation"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/sirikit\/inreservation","type":"link"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10068-Whats-new-in-SiriKit-and-Shortcuts":{"abstract":[{"text":"Get a quick overview of everything new in Siri and Shortcuts to help people get more out of your app: We’ll demonstrate how you can design visually rich conversations, feel at home with the operating system by designing for the new compact Siri UI, and provide an overview of all the ways we’ve made it even easier for people to organize and set up actions from your apps.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10068-Whats-new-in-SiriKit-and-Shortcuts","title":"What’s new in SiriKit and Shortcuts","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10068-whats-new-in-sirikit-and-shortcuts"},"https://schema.org/docs/documents.html":{"title":"schema.org","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"schema.org","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/schema.org\/docs\/documents.html","url":"https:\/\/schema.org\/docs\/documents.html","type":"link"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"kind":"symbol"},"WWDC20-10197-overview":{"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDC20-10197-overview.png"}],"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC20-10197-overview"},"WWDC20-10197-itemReference":{"identifier":"WWDC20-10197-itemReference","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDC20-10197-itemReference.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/zntfdr":{"type":"topic","title":"Federico Zanetello (332 notes)","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/zntfdr","abstract":[{"text":"Software engineer with a strong passion for well-written code, thought-out composable architectures, automation, tests, and more.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr","images":[{"type":"card","identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg"},{"type":"icon","identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg"}],"role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10088-Design-for-intelligence-Discover-new-opportunities":{"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how extensibility is key to surfacing the most important features of your app into new entry points of the operating system. And discover how — by breaking out of the constraints of a monolithic container — your app can see increased engagement through suggestions on the lock screen, in Calendar, and by enabling voice interactions.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10088-Design-for-intelligence-Discover-new-opportunities","title":"Design for intelligence: Discover new opportunities","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10088-design-for-intelligence-discover-new-opportunities"},"https://developer.apple.com/wwdc20/10197":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc20\/10197","checksum":null,"type":"download","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc20\/10197"},"WWDC20.jpeg":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDC20.jpeg"}],"identifier":"WWDC20.jpeg","type":"image","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10087-Design-for-intelligence-Make-friends-with-The-System":{"role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10087-Design-for-intelligence-Make-friends-with-The-System","title":"Design for intelligence: Make friends with “The System”","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10087-design-for-intelligence-make-friends-with-the-system","kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The building blocks of the intelligent system are simple: Define, learn, execute. Discover how you can use intents to define your app’s key features, create donations to help the system learn and make predictions about the future, and implement extensibility to ensure your app is ready to execute at just the right moment. Learn from teams at Apple about how their technologies use intents and donations in different ways, all for the same goal: to make the everyday easier."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC23-10052-Discover-Calendar-and-EventKit":{"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc23-10052-discover-calendar-and-eventkit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Discover how you can bring Calendar into your app and help people better manage their time. Find out how to create new events from your app, fetch events, and implement a virtual conference extension. We’ll also take you through some of the changes to calendar access levels that help your app stay connected without compromising the privacy of someone’s calendar data."}],"title":"Discover Calendar and EventKit","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC23-10052-Discover-Calendar-and-EventKit","type":"topic"},"https://developer.apple.com/contact/request/siri-events/":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/contact\/request\/siri-events\/","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"developer.apple.com","type":"text"}],"title":"developer.apple.com","type":"link","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/contact\/request\/siri-events\/"},"zntfdr":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/zntfdr.jpeg"}],"identifier":"zntfdr","alt":"Profile image of Federico Zanetello","type":"image"},"zntfdr.jpeg":{"identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/zntfdr.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10086-Design-for-intelligence-Apps-evolved":{"abstract":[{"text":"Intelligence is a core part of building a great modern app. App extensions, Siri suggestions, voice, widgets, App Clips — we’ve designed all of these features to help make everyday tasks easier for people who use our platforms. Learn about the origins of the intelligent system experience, and find out how integrating intelligently with the system can help make your app more convenient, relevant, and intuitive, making your features the focus.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10086-Design-for-intelligence-Apps-evolved","title":"Design for intelligence: Apps, evolved","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10086-design-for-intelligence-apps-evolved"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"image"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","title":"Contributions are welcome!","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributions are welcome!","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"WWDC20-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDC20-Icon.png"}],"identifier":"WWDC20-Icon.png","type":"image","alt":null},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/sirikit/ininteraction":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/sirikit\/ininteraction","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"INInteraction","type":"codeVoice"}],"title":"INInteraction","type":"link","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/sirikit\/ininteraction"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20":{"type":"topic","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC20-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC20.jpeg","type":"card"}],"title":"WWDC20","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 12, Swift 5.3, iOS 14, macOS 11 (Big Sur), tvOS 14, watchOS 7.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"New APIs: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WidgetKit"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StoreKit Testing"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20","role":"collectionGroup"},"https://github.com/zntfdr":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GitHub"}],"type":"link","title":"GitHub"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-243-Integrating-with-Siri-Event-Suggestions":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-243-Integrating-with-Siri-Event-Suggestions","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-243-integrating-with-siri-event-suggestions","title":"Integrating with Siri Event Suggestions","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Siri is the intelligence behind displaying what someone needs to know about at just the right moment. In iOS 13, we’re extending this capability to allow your apps to let Siri know when a reservation has been made and Siri can elevate checking in at the right time. Siri can also provide directions to the reservation in Maps, add the event to Calendar, and more. Discover how you can add the power of Siri Event Suggestions to your apps."}],"role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10200-Design-for-intelligence-Meet-people-where-they-are":{"abstract":[{"text":"Understand what motivates people to use your app — and how you can use system intelligence to help them and achieve your own goals as a developer. We’ll take a look at a typical person’s journey to better understand how an app can become a key part of their routine — and why some apps just don’t stick. Learn how you can provide the right kind of value at the right time to help them in their everyday tasks, and how your app and the system can evolve alongside them.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10200-Design-for-intelligence-Meet-people-where-they-are","title":"Design for intelligence: Meet people where they are","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10200-design-for-intelligence-meet-people-where-they-are"},"https://zntfdr.dev":{"title":"Blog","identifier":"https:\/\/zntfdr.dev","type":"link","url":"https:\/\/zntfdr.dev","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Blog"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/sirikit/ingetreservationdetailsintent":{"title":"INGetReservationDetailsIntent","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"INGetReservationDetailsIntent"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/sirikit\/ingetreservationdetailsintent","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/sirikit\/ingetreservationdetailsintent","type":"link"}}}